    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Insignia of warriors in Nahua culture reflecting the person's rank and experience in battle. Generally used to refer to the feathered suits that encased the body, arms, and legs, however, the term also applies to various accoutrements including headdresses, large emblems carried on a frame worn on the back, as well as banners and shields.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
